cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.DS

This paper deals with detecting anomalies in DNS traffic, which is a common technique used in cyber attacks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves network analysis and machine learning techniques, which could fall under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of visual aids and quantitative analysis could also place this paper under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
